<div class="comment odd"><div class="comment-inner clear-block">

      <h3 class="title">
      <a href="/node/361#comment-682" class="active">A few minor corrections</a>          </h3>
  
  
  
  <div class="submitted">
    Submitted by Craig Walls on Fri, 2006-10-20 22:04.  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <p>Just noticed a few more things of note with regard to this OSGi archetype...</p>
<p>First, the "-DarchetypeId" parameter (next to the last one in Adrian's original post) should be "-DartifactId". </p>
<p>Also, I said that once you run the archetype with the "-DremoteRepository" the first time you won't have to use it again. That's not exactly true...because it's a SNAPSHOT version, you'll need to use the "-DremoteRepository" parameter once every day (or maybe change your Maven configuration's SNAPSHOT policy).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="links">
      <ul class="links"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>    </div>
  
