      <h3 class="title">
      <a href="/node/361#comment-1020" class="active">remoteRepository doesn&#039;t work for MAVEN 2.0.4</a>          </h3>
  
  
  
  <div class="submitted">
    Submitted by kelmo on Mon, 2006-10-23 06:04.  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <p>I tried to follow your tips and wasn't been able to achieved the installation of the plugins with the -DremoteRepository (also tried repositories in settings.xml)<br />
So I've install "by hand" (using install:install-file<br />
). Once I've installed spring-osgi-bundle-archetype and import the project into my Eclipse workspace, I had to install (to avoid eclipse classpath errors) also:<br />
- commons-logging.osgi<br />
- spring-beans<br />
- spring-context<br />
- spring-core (in the repository it appears with a bomb ico!!! What does it mean?)<br />
- spring-mock</p>
<p>Now the Eclipse project is OK</p>
